body:
    $ cat bug.go
    package p

    type pt struct{ x, y int }

    var _ = map[pt]pt{pt{0, 0}: pt{1, 1}}

    $ gofmt -s bug.go
    package p

    type pt struct{ x, y int }

    var _ = map[pt]pt{pt{0, 0}: {1, 1}}

Note it simplified `pt{1, 1}` to just `{1, 1}`, but left `pt{0, 0}` as is.  It seems to have missed [Go 1.5's language change to map literals](https://golang.org/doc/go1.5#map_literals).

/cc @griesemer
